=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 03, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gre1665702891639.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gre1665702891639.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gre1665702891639.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gre1665702891639\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Importing a Type Library\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"gre1665702891639__importing_a_type_library_113230\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">To simplify communication with external objects, you can import type library information using the command line switch <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/sti</span> with <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/mwr</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=com</code>.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gre1665702891639__p_d35306e1_d35307e1_d35308e1\">You can import a type library either by entering the <var class=\"keyword varname\">PathToTypeLibrary</var>, or by using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/pid</span> subswitch with the logical name (ProgId) that maps to the type library. For example, enter a command according to the following syntax in the command line:</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gre1665702891639__p_d35309e1_d35310e1_d35311e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/sti</span> {<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/verbose</span>} <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/mwr=com</span>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">PathToTypeLibrary</var>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gre1665702891639__p_d35312e1_d35313e1_d35314e1\">or</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gre1665702891639__p_d35315e1_d35316e1_d35317e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/sti</span> {<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/verbose</span>} <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/mwr=com</span>\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/pid</span>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">ProgId</var>{<code class=\"ph codeph\">:</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Prefix</var>}</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gre1665702891639__p_d35318e1_d35319e1_d35320e1\">where:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gre1665702891639__li_d18080e1_d18081e1_d18082e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/verbose</span>—produces a detailed description of the imported data. By default, a brief description is shown. Optional.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gre1665702891639__li_d18083e1_d18084e1_d18085e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">PathToTypeLibrary</var>—path to a type library.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gre1665702891639__li_d18086e1_d18087e1_d18088e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/pid</span>—indicates that <var class=\"keyword varname\">ProgId</var> is a logical name that maps to a type library, for example <code class=\"ph codeph\">word.document</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gre1665702891639__li_d18089e1_d18090e1_d18091e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">:</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Prefix</var>—causes the prefix name to precede the signature names for each type definition found in the type library.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/khj1665702753156.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>/sti</a><p>Import interface definitions to integrate call-out to web services, various types of middleware, or to generate C call-in stub code for all types of components.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527984\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527984\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Importing a Type Library Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 03, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Importing a Type Library To simplify communication with external objects, you can import type library information using the command line switch /sti with /mwr =com . You can import a type library either by entering the PathToTypeLibrary , or by using the /pid subswitch with the logical name (ProgId) that maps to the type library. For example, enter a command according to the following syntax in the command line: /sti { /verbose } /mwr=com PathToTypeLibrary or /sti { /verbose } /mwr=com /pid ProgId { : Prefix } where: /verbose —produces a detailed description of the imported data. By default, a brief description is shown. Optional. PathToTypeLibrary —path to a type library. /pid —indicates that ProgId is a logical name that maps to a type library, for example word.document : Prefix —causes the prefix name to precede the signature names for each type definition found in the type library. Related Links /sti Import interface definitions to integrate call-out to web services, various types of middleware, or to generate C call-in stub code for all types of components. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}